# SentinelGRC

> An open-source Governance, Risk, and Compliance (GRC) automation framework built with PowerShell, SQLite, and Power BI.

---

## Overview

SentinelGRC is an extensible PowerShell framework designed to automate technical compliance validation, evidence collection, vulnerability correlation, asset inventory, and reporting across multiple cybersecurity frameworks.

The project was created to provide a lightweight, vendor-neutral alternative to commercial Governance, Risk, and Compliance platforms while remaining modular, transparent, and extensible.

Unlike traditional vulnerability scanners or compliance utilities that focus on a single standard, SentinelGRC normalizes technical evidence and maps that evidence to multiple frameworks simultaneously.

Supported framework mappings include:

- CMMC 2.0
- NIST SP 800-53 Rev. 5
- NIST SP 800-171 Rev. 3
- NIST SP 800-172
- DISA STIG
- SCAP
- CIS Benchmarks

The framework is intended for:

- Security Engineers
- GRC Analysts
- Compliance Officers
- System Administrators
- DoD Contractors
- Managed Security Service Providers
- Internal Audit Teams

---

# Design Philosophy

SentinelGRC is built around four guiding principles.

## Collect Once

Evidence should be collected a single time.

A password policy check, for example, should never be rewritten for every compliance framework.

One technical check can satisfy controls across multiple standards.

---

## Normalize Everything

Every technical check returns a standardized object.

This allows reporting, dashboards, database storage, and framework mapping to remain independent of the individual checks.

---

## Modular by Design

Every compliance check exists as an independent module.

Adding a new check never requires modifications to the core engine.

---

## Vendor Neutral

The framework intentionally avoids dependencies on commercial GRC platforms.

All data remains portable and human-readable.

