# Features

## Asset Inventory

Collect:

- Computer Name
- Operating System
- IP Address
- MAC Address
- Domain
- Installed Software
- Running Services
- CPU
- Memory
- TPM
- BitLocker
- Secure Boot
- Local Administrators
- Installed Updates

---

## Compliance Checking

Technical evidence collection includes:

- Password Policies
- Audit Policy
- Firewall Configuration
- Windows Defender
- Microsoft Defender for Endpoint
- LAPS
- Credential Guard
- BitLocker
- Secure Boot
- AppLocker
- TLS Configuration
- SMB Configuration
- Remote Desktop
- Windows Services
- Registry Settings
- PowerShell Logging

---

## Vulnerability Correlation

Import findings from:

- Nessus
- OpenVAS
- Microsoft Defender
- Qualys
- Rapid7
- SCAP
- STIG Viewer

---

## Framework Mapping

One technical check can satisfy multiple frameworks.

Example:

Password Complexity

↓

Maps automatically to:

- CMMC
- NIST 800-171
- NIST 800-53
- STIG
- CIS

---

## Reporting

Generate:

- Excel
- CSV
- JSON
- SQLite
- Power BI datasets

